  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UAE National Air Emissions Monitoring Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objectives are to i.) track the sources and volume of key pollutants to guide policy making on air quality monitoring and management and ii.) lay the groundwork for developing the UAE National Air Quality Strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While the emirates of Abu Dhabi and Dubai have achieved considerable progress in building their own local inventories, the other emirates are lagging behind due to lack of technical capacity. Moreover, a difference in methodologies used by Abu Dhabi and Dubai calls for a more unified approach on air quality monitoring across the country. To address this problem, GGGI worked with MOCCAE for the Phase 1 of the project in 2018, which involved finalizing a unified&#x202F;inventory methodology for all seven emirates. In Phase 2, GGGI provided technical assistance in building the air pollutants emissions inventory covering all seven emirates (local governments). GGGI led the development of the inventory by managing the overall project activities, performing analytical work, leading the delivery of outputs, supporting data collection and processing, facilitating stakeholder engagement and communication, and doing quality checks of the technical deliverables from consultants. The project also involved the preparatory work for the development of the Air Quality Strategy, a federal policy document that will outline the UAE&apos;s strategic priorities in tackling air pollution.</narrative>
  </description>
